COFCO Says Ethanol Use in China Won’t Harm Grain Security, Xinhua Reports

-- B y   B l o o m b e r g   N e w s
-- 
2011-04-21T08:08:16Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-04-21/cofco-says-ethanol-use-in-china-won-t-harm-grain-security-xinhua-reports.html
Ethanol development in  China  won’t
harm the country’s grain security, the Xinhua News Agency
reported today, citing Yue Guojun, assistant president of COFCO
Ltd., China’s biggest grain-trading company.  Use of crops to make the biofuel accounts for less than 1
percent of China’s total grain output, Yue was quoted as saying
by Xinhua.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Bloomberg News at 
 rdobson4@bloomberg.net  